{
  "texts": [
    "A simple powerlaw decrease of the BLR brightness with distance to the central black hole is assumed, as well as simple geometries, such as a keplerian disc, a polar or equatorial wind, and various velocity fields able to reproduce emission line profiles (e.g.",
    "Murray et al. 1995; Murray and Chiang 1997).",
    "To simulate such profiles, one could use analytical models (e.g.",
    "Abajas et al. 2002) or radiative transfer simulations that can produce the light profile of the BLR for arbitrary velocity slice(s) (e.g.",
    "For radiative transfer models, the photo-ionizing source of light is supposed to be the quasar accretion disc, assumed to be smaller and have the same inclination as the BLR."
  ]
}